{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783916515701,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeMi6luqm6mHU9Lf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_W9euVZ4tkOfLNfqdcTWfyHHb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-verify/lineages/xhigh-c/deep-review-strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":500},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-verify/lineages/xhigh-c/deep-review-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Strategy - xhigh-c\n3: description: Detached lineage strategy for the sk-code split-document template-alignment verification review.\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # Deep Review Strategy - xhigh-c\n7: \n8: ## 1. TOPIC\n9: \n10: Review `.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment` against its shipped 163 Markdown deliverables.\n11: \n12: ## 2. REVIEW CHARTER\n13: \n14: - Target: `.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment` (`spec-folder`)\n15: - Scope: the 163 Markdown files under the configured reference/asset roots, with canonical packet docs used for traceability.\n16: - Non-goals: implementation fixes, files outside the configured roots, surface `SKILL.md` header conformance, and changes to the reviewed target.\n17: - Stop condition: dispatch all four configured iterations; convergence before iteration 4 is telemetry only.\n18: \n19: <!-- ANCHOR:review-dimensions -->\n20: ## 3. REVIEW DIMENSIONS (remaining)\n21: - [x] correctness\n22: - [ ] security\n23: - [ ] traceability\n24: - [ ] maintainability\n25: \n26: <!-- /ANCHOR:review-dimensions -->\n27: \n28: <!-- ANCHOR:completed-dimensions -->\n29: ## 4. COMPLETED DIMENSIONS\n30: - Iteration 1 — correctness — 88/100 — CONDITIONAL (1 P1, 1 P2; full 163-file deterministic scan plus direct adjudication)\n31: \n32: <!-- /ANCHOR:completed-dimensions -->\n33: \n34: <!-- ANCHOR:running-findings -->\n35: ## 5. RUNNING FINDINGS\n36: - P0 (Blockers): 0\n37: - P1 (Required): 1\n38: - P2 (Suggestions): 1\n39: - Resolved: 0\n40: \n41: <!-- /ANCHOR:running-findings -->\n42: \n43: ## 6. WHAT WORKED\n44: \n45: - Iteration 1: Forced-type validation plus an independent opening-shape/link/frontmatter scan covered all 163 configured files; direct rereads confirmed the single wrapper defect and the seven-instance intro-length advisory.\n46: \n47: ## 7. WHAT FAILED\n48: \n49: - Memory trigger and focused context retrieval timed out at initialization; direct packet evidence is the fallback.\n50: - Iteration 1: `validate_document.py` alone could not prove R3 because its no-numbered-H2 path accepts the malformed Rust reference; validation success was retained as counterevidence rather than treated as conformance proof.\n51: \n52: ## 8. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n53: \n54: - Runtime behavior and executable security paths: the packet is documentation-only and claims no runtime changes.\n55: \n56: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n57: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n58: - Iteration 1 — full-corpus frontmatter/version, filename, wrapper-order, exact intro/Purpose duplication, and scoped relative-link scan: PRODUCTIVE and complete for correctness; do not repeat this exact structural sweep.\n59: \n60: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n61: \n62: ## 10A. SATURATED / SWEPT DIMENSIONS AND EXPANSION FRONTIER\n63: - Completed pivots: 1\n64: - Failed pivots: 0\n65: - Audited overrides: 0\n66: - Swept: correctness structural-contract sweep\n67: - Pivot lineage: iteration 1 correctness -> iteration 2 security\n68: - Remaining frontier: security, traceability, maintainability\n69: \n70: ## 11. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n71: \n72: - Do not widen into unrelated sk-code skills or runtime implementation.\n73: \n74: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n75: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n76: - Dimension: security\n77: - Focus area: instruction examples, trust boundaries, unsafe command patterns, and secret-handling guidance in the configured corpus.\n78: - Reason: correctness received a complete deterministic structural pass and direct evidence adjudication.\n79: - Rotation status: correctness complete; security next.\n80: - Blocked/productive carry-forward: preserve the productive 163-file inventory; do not repeat the exhausted structural wrapper scan.\n81: - Required evidence: exact unsafe guidance or explicit clean counterevidence with file:line citations.\n82: \n83: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n84: \n85: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n86: \n87: ### Bounded Context Snapshot\n88: \n89: - Target pointers: six configured reference/asset roots totaling 163 Markdown files; packet docs are the governing claims.\n90: - Behavior claims: five-field frontmatter, four-part versions, snake_case names, H1/intro/Overview structure, preserved substantive content, and repaired in-hub references.\n91: - Reuse and conventions: create-skill reference/asset templates and `validate_document.py` are the stated authority.\n92: - Review risks and gaps: prior post-ship review remediated duplicated Purpose text and narrowed a broken-link claim; memory MCP timed out; no packet resource map exists.\n93: - Iteration 1 carry-forward: one active P1 wrapper omission; seven advisory intro-length mismatches; R4 content preservation remains unverified without a pre-transformation baseline; prior inventory distribution was stale although its total remained 163.\n94: - Out of scope: surface `SKILL.md` header shape and unrelated deep-loop artifacts.\n95: \n96: ## 13. CROSS-REFERENCE STATUS\n97: \n98: | Protocol | Level | Status | Iteration | Notes |\n99: |----------|-------|--------|-----------|-------|\n100: | `spec_code` | core | failed | 1 | R3 wrapper mismatch confirmed in one Rust reference; seven intro-length advisories. |\n101: | `checklist_evidence` | core | failed | 1 | Validator pass is real but misses no-H2 wrapper omissions, so it