NAL (1 P1, 1 P2; full 163-file deterministic scan plus direct adjudication)\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:completed-dimensions -->\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:running-findings -->\n## 5. RUNNING FINDINGS\n- P0 (Blockers): 0\n- P1 (Required): 1\n- P2 (Suggestions): 1\n- Resolved: 0\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:running-findings -->\n\n## 6. WHAT WORKED\n\n- Iteration 1: Forced-type validation plus an independent opening-shape/link/frontmatter scan covered all 163 configured files; direct rereads confirmed the single wrapper defect and the seven-instance intro-length advisory.\n\n## 7. WHAT FAILED\n\n- Memory trigger and focused context retrieval timed out at initialization; direct packet evidence is the fallback.\n- Iteration 1: `validate_document.py` alone could not prove R3 because its no-numbered-H2 path accepts the malformed Rust reference; validation success was retained as counterevidence rather than treated as conformance proof.\n\n## 8. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n\n- Runtime behavior and executable security paths: the packet is documentation-only and claims no runtime changes.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n- Iteration 1 — full-corpus frontmatter/version, filename, wrapper-order, exact intro/Purpose duplication, and scoped relative-link scan: PRODUCTIVE and complete for correctness; do not repeat this exact structural sweep.\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n## 10A. SATURATED / SWEPT DIMENSIONS AND EXPANSION FRONTIER\n- Completed pivots: 1\n- Failed pivots: 0\n- Audited overrides: 0\n- Swept: correctness structural-contract sweep\n- Pivot lineage: iteration 1 correctness -> iteration 2 security\n- Remaining frontier: security, traceability, maintainability\n\n## 11. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n\n- Do not widen into unrelated sk-code skills or runtime implementation.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n- Dimension: security\n- Focus area: instruction examples, trust boundaries, unsafe command patterns, and secret-handling guidance in the configured corpus.\n- Reason: correctness received a complete deterministic structural pass and direct evidence adjudication.\n- Rotation status: correctness complete; security next.\n- Blocked/productive carry-forward: preserve the productive 163-file inventory; do not repeat the exhausted structural wrapper scan.\n- Required evidence: exact unsafe guidance or explicit clean counterevidence with file:line citations.\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n\n### Bounded Context Snapshot\n\n- Target pointers: six configured reference/asset roots totaling 163 Markdown files; packet docs are the governing claims.\n- Behavior claims: five-field frontmatter, four-part versions, snake_case names, H1/intro/Overview structure, preserved substantive content, and repaired in-hub references.\n- Reuse and conventions: create-skill reference/asset templates and `validate_document.py` are the stated authority.\n- Review risks and gaps: prior post-ship review remediated duplicated Purpose text and narrowed a broken-link claim; memory MCP timed out; no packet resource map exists.\n- Iteration 1 carry-forward: one active P1 wrapper omission; seven advisory intro-length mismatches; R4 content preservation remains unverified without a pre-transformation baseline; prior inventory distribution was stale although its total remained 163.\n- Out of scope: surface `SKILL.md` header shape and unrelated deep-loop artifacts.\n\n## 13. CROSS-REFERENCE STATUS\n\n| Protocol | Level | Status | Iteration | Notes |\n|----------|-------|--------|-----------|-------|\n| `spec_code` | core | failed | 1 | R3 wrapper mismatch confirmed in one Rust reference; seven intro-length advisories. |\n| `checklist_evidence` | core | failed | 1 | Validator pass is real but misses no-H2 wrapper omissions, so it does not prove R3. |\n| `feature_catalog_code` | overlay | pending | - | Check applicability and evidence. |\n| `playbook_capability` | overlay | pending | - | Check applicability and evidence. |\n| `skill_agent` | overlay | notApplicable | - | Target type is spec-folder. |\n| `agent_cross_runtime` | overlay | notApplicable | - | Target type is spec-folder. |\n\n## 14. FILES UNDER REVIEW\n\n| Root | Files | Dimensions Reviewed | Status |\n|------|------:|---------------------|--------|\n| `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/**/*.md` | 50 | correctness | reviewed-with-findings |\n| `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/assets/**/*.md` | 15 | correctness | reviewed-clean |\n| `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/**/*.md` | 86 | correctness | reviewed-with-advisory |\n| `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/assets/**/*.md` | 9 | correctness | reviewed-clean |\n| `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/references/**/*.md` | 0 | - | notApplicable |\n| `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-quality/assets/**/*.md` | 3 | correctness | reviewed-clean |\n\n## 15. REVIEW BOUNDARIES\n\n- Max iterations: 4\n- Convergence threshold: 0.1\n- Stop policy: max-iterations\n- Session lineage: `fanout-xhigh-c-1783915428096-y929h9`, generation 1, lineageMode new\n- Artifact root: `.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-verify/lineages/xhigh-c`\n- Writable boundary: artifact root only\n- Resource map coverage gate: skipped because the packet has no `resource-map.md`","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":126,"totalLines":126,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-verify/lineages/xhigh-c/deep-review-strategy.md","time":{"start":1783916515697,"end":1783916515700}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0ca0e827e081546a016a5467e35588819181f0bc7de1825720"}},"id":"prt_f59b5d0d9001OWwMBuxAuqeYCX","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeMi6luqm6mHU9Lf","messageID":"msg_f59b5a477001LseiP3bv36pWR1"}}
