{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783917896593,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeMi6luqm6mHU9Lf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_bGsfEH7HE1BMcRXIW76dF72j","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-verify/lineages/xhigh-c/deep-review-strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":550},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-verify/lineages/xhigh-c/deep-review-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Strategy - xhigh-c\n3: description: Detached lineage strategy for the sk-code split-document template-alignment verification review.\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # Deep Review Strategy - xhigh-c\n7: \n8: ## 1. TOPIC\n9: \n10: Review `.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment` against the Markdown deliverables selected by its configured scope globs.\n11: \n12: ## 2. REVIEW CHARTER\n13: \n14: - Target: `.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment` (`spec-folder`)\n15: - Scope: the Markdown files under the configured reference/asset roots, with canonical packet docs used for traceability. Independent iteration-3 enumeration confirms 163 lexical-unique Markdown path entries (160 resolved document targets because three shared workflow documents are each exposed by two surface symlinks).\n16: - Non-goals: implementation fixes, files outside the configured roots, surface `SKILL.md` header conformance, and changes to the reviewed target.\n17: - Stop condition: dispatch all four configured iterations; convergence before iteration 4 is telemetry only.\n18: \n19: <!-- ANCHOR:review-dimensions -->\n20: ## 3. REVIEW DIMENSIONS (remaining)\n21: - [ ] maintainability\n22: \n23: <!-- /ANCHOR:review-dimensions -->\n24: \n25: <!-- ANCHOR:completed-dimensions -->\n26: ## 4. COMPLETED DIMENSIONS\n27: - [x] correctness\n28: - [x] security\n29: - [x] traceability\n30: \n31: <!-- /ANCHOR:completed-dimensions -->\n32: \n33: <!-- ANCHOR:running-findings -->\n34: ## 5. RUNNING FINDINGS\n35: - P0 (Blockers): 0\n36: - P1 (Required): 2\n37: - P2 (Suggestions): 2\n38: - Resolved: 0\n39: \n40: <!-- /ANCHOR:running-findings -->\n41: \n42: ## 6. WHAT WORKED\n43: \n44: - Iteration 1: Forced-type validation plus an independent opening-shape/link/frontmatter scan covered all 163 configured files; direct rereads confirmed the single wrapper defect and the seven-instance intro-length advisory.\n45: - Iteration 2: Scope-corrected security searches plus direct counterevidence reads isolated contradictory session-cookie guidance and a CDN-loader hardening gap while ruling out endorsed hardcoded secrets, client-only authorization, direct input execution, and destructive shell bootstrap guidance.\n46: - Iteration 3: Independent enumeration reconciled the command-owned Markdown scope at 163 lexical entries, executed both core traceability protocols by narrow evidence reads, and classified both overlays as evidence-backed notApplicable without repeating saturated sweeps.\n47: \n48: ## 7. WHAT FAILED\n49: \n50: - Memory trigger and focused context retrieval timed out at initialization; direct packet evidence is the fallback.\n51: - Iteration 1: `validate_document.py` alone could not prove R3 because its no-numbered-H2 path accepts the malformed Rust reference; validation success was retained as counterevidence rather than treated as conformance proof.\n52: - Iteration 2: An initial directory-level discovery search surfaced six non-Markdown asset files outside the rendered `**/*.md` scope. Those hits were discarded, the search was rerun with `--glob '*.md'`, and no finding relies on the excluded files.\n53: - Iteration 3: Iteration 2's 157-count explanation was disproved. Ripgrep-style discovery omitted six symlink entries; all 163 configured matches are Markdown, representing 160 unique resolved document targets.\n54: \n55: ## 8. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n56: \n57: - Runtime behavior and executable security paths: the packet is documentation-only and claims no runtime changes.\n58: \n59: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n60: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n61: - Iteration 3 protocol-resolution note: the rendered traceability prompt required current core execution and evidence-backed overlay classification. This did not retry the blocked full-corpus approaches: core protocols used narrow current cross-reference reads, while both overlays were classified `notApplicable` from packet scope. Historical entries below remain as prior-iteration provenance; current protocol status is recorded in Section 13.\n62: ### `checklist_evidence` (core): **failed, carried forward without re-execution** -- the blocked validator-evidence approach was not retried. -- BLOCKED (iteration 2, 1 attempts)\n63: - What was tried: `checklist_evidence` (core): **failed, carried forward without re-execution** -- the blocked validator-evidence approach was not retried.\n64: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n65: - Do NOT retry: `checklist_evidence` (core): **failed, carried forward without re-execution** -- the blocked validator-evidence approach was not retried.\n66: \n67: ### `checklist_evidence` (core): **failed** -- `checklist.md:49` records a real 163/163 validator pass, but that checker does not establish the wrapper invariant for a file with no numbered H2. The completion evidence is therefore insufficient for R3. -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n68: - What was tried: `checklist_evidence` (core): **failed** -- `checklist.md:49` records a real 163/163 validator pass, but that checker does not establish the wrapper invariant for a file with no numbered H2. The completion evidence is therefore insufficient for R3.\n69: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n70: - Do NOT retry: `checklist_evidence` (core): **failed** -- `checklist.md:49` records a real 163/163 validator pass, but that checker does not establish the wrapper invariant for a file with no numbered H2. The completion evidence is therefore insufficient for R3.\n71: \n72: ### `feature_catalog_code` / `playbook_capability` (overlay): **pending** -- not executed in the security dimension; their strategy entries are marked blocked and must not be retried without a later protocol-resolution decision. -- BLOCKED (iteration 2, 1 attempts)\n73: - What was tried: `feature_catalog_code` / `playbook_capability` (overlay): **pending** -- not executed in the security dimension; their strategy entries are marked blocked and must not be retried without a later protocol-resolution decision.\n74: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n75: - Do NOT retry: `feature_catalog_code` / `playbook_capability` (overlay): **pending** -- not executed in the security dimension; their strategy entries are marked blocked and must not be retried without a later protocol-resolution decision.\n76: \n77: ### `feature_catalog_code` / `playbook_capability`: **pending** -- not required for the correctness focus and preserved for a later traceability iteration. -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n78: - What was tried: `feature_catalog_code` / `playbook_capability`: **pending** -- not required for the correctness focus and preserved for a later traceability iteration.\n79: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n80: - Do NOT retry: `feature_catalog_code` / `playbook_capability`: **pending** -- not required for the correctness focus and preserved for a later traceability iteration.\n81: \n82: ### `skill_agent` / `agent_cross_runtime`: **notApplicable** -- the target is a spec-folder/document corpus, not an agent definition. -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n83: - What was tried: `skill_agent` / `agent_cross_runtime`: **notApplicable** -- the target is a spec-f