ass: ruled out across 163 files.\n141: \n142: ### Security evidence: **complete for this iteration** -- each active security finding has direct Markdown file:line evidence and the P1 received an in-iteration skeptic/referee pass. -- BLOCKED (iteration 2, 1 attempts)\n143: - What was tried: Security evidence: **complete for this iteration** -- each active security finding has direct Markdown file:line evidence and the P1 received an in-iteration skeptic/referee pass.\n144: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n145: - Do NOT retry: Security evidence: **complete for this iteration** -- each active security finding has direct Markdown file:line evidence and the P1 received an in-iteration skeptic/referee pass.\n146: \n147: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n148: \n149: ## 10A. SATURATED / SWEPT DIMENSIONS AND EXPANSION FRONTIER\n150: - Completed pivots: 2\n151: - Failed pivots: 0\n152: - Audited overrides: 0\n153: - Swept: correctness structural-contract sweep; security unsafe-guidance sweep\n154: - Pivot lineage: iteration 1 correctness -> iteration 2 security -> iteration 3 traceability\n155: - Remaining frontier: maintainability\n156: \n157: ## 11. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n158: \n159: - Do not widen into unrelated sk-code skills or runtime implementation.\n160: \n161: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n162: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n163: - Dimension: `maintainability`\n164: - Focus area: documentation clarity, pattern consistency, and safe follow-on change cost within the configured Markdown scope.\n165: - Reason: traceability now has an independently reconciled inventory, executed core protocols, and evidence-backed overlay classifications.\n166: - Rotation status: correctness, security, and traceability complete; maintainability is the final unchecked dimension.\n167: - Blocked/productive carry-forward: preserve the 163-path/160-target symlink distinction and active findings; do not repeat saturated correctness/security sweeps.\n168: - Required evidence: focused maintainability reads with exact file:line citations and narrow same-class checks only where a candidate appears.\n169: \n170: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n171: \n172: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n173: \n174: ### Bounded Context Snapshot\n175: \n176: - Target pointers: six configured reference/asset roots totaling 163 Markdown path entries and 160 resolved document targets; packet docs are the governing claims.\n177: - Behavior claims: five-field frontmatter, four-part versions, snake_case names, H1/intro/Overview structure, preserved substantive content, and repaired in-hub references.\n178: - Reuse and conventions: create-skill reference/asset templates and `validate_document.py` are the stated authority.\n179: - Review risks and gaps: prior post-ship review remediated duplicated Purpose text and narrowed a broken-link claim; memory MCP timed out; no packet resource map exists.\n180: - Iteration 1 carry-forward: one active P1 wrapper omission; seven advisory intro-length mismatches; R4 content preservation remains unverified without a pre-transformation baseline; prior inventory distribution was stale although its total remained 163.\n181: - Iteration 2 carry-forward: one new P1 for contradictory JavaScript session-cookie guidance and one new P2 for CDN-loader integrity/allowlist hardening.\n182: - Iteration 3 carry-forward: the explicit Markdown globs independently match 163 path entries, not 157; six symlink paths expose three shared workflow documents under both surfaces, yielding 160 resolved targets. Core protocols remain failed on the active R3 mismatch; both overlays are notApplicable by packet scope.\n183: - Out of scope: surface `SKILL.md` header shape and unrelated deep-loop artifacts.\n184: \n185: ## 13. CROSS-REFERENCE STATUS\n186: \n187: | Protocol | Level | Status | Iteration | Notes |\n188: |----------|-------|--------|-----------|-------|\n189: | `spec_code` | core | failed | 1, 3 | Narrow current reread confirms the active R3 wrapper mis