{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783918489559,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeMi6luqm6mHU9Lf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_wHpcx2DGtkF9Yp6YjVrYFBQP","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-verify/lineages/xhigh-c/deep-review-strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":650},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment/review/xhigh-verify/lineages/xhigh-c/deep-review-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Strategy - xhigh-c\n3: description: Detached lineage strategy for the sk-code split-document template-alignment verification review.\n4: ---\n5: \n6: # Deep Review Strategy - xhigh-c\n7: \n8: ## 1. TOPIC\n9: \n10: Review `.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment` against the Markdown deliverables selected by its configured scope globs.\n11: \n12: ## 2. REVIEW CHARTER\n13: \n14: - Target: `.opencode/specs/sk-code/019-split-doc-template-alignment` (`spec-folder`)\n15: - Scope: the Markdown files under the configured reference/asset roots, with canonical packet docs used for traceability. Independent iteration-3 enumeration confirms 163 lexical-unique Markdown path entries (160 resolved document targets because three shared workflow documents are each exposed by two surface symlinks).\n16: - Non-goals: implementation fixes, files outside the configured roots, surface `SKILL.md` header conformance, and changes to the reviewed target.\n17: - Stop condition: dispatch all four configured iterations; convergence before iteration 4 is telemetry only.\n18: \n19: <!-- ANCHOR:review-dimensions -->\n20: ## 3. REVIEW DIMENSIONS (remaining)\n21: - None; all configured dimensions are complete.\n22: \n23: <!-- /ANCHOR:review-dimensions -->\n24: \n25: <!-- ANCHOR:completed-dimensions -->\n26: ## 4. COMPLETED DIMENSIONS\n27: - [x] correctness\n28: - [x] security\n29: - [x] traceability\n30: - [x] maintainability\n31: \n32: <!-- /ANCHOR:completed-dimensions -->\n33: \n34: <!-- ANCHOR:running-findings -->\n35: ## 5. RUNNING FINDINGS\n36: - P0 (Blockers): 0\n37: - P1 (Required): 2\n38: - P2 (Suggestions): 3\n39: - Resolved: 0\n40: \n41: <!-- /ANCHOR:running-findings -->\n42: \n43: ## 6. WHAT WORKED\n44: \n45: - Iteration 1: Forced-type validation plus an independent opening-shape/link/frontmatter scan covered all 163 configured files; direct rereads confirmed the single wrapper defect and the seven-instance intro-length advisory.\n46: - Iteration 2: Scope-corrected security searches plus direct counterevidence reads isolated contradictory session-cookie guidance and a CDN-loader hardening gap while ruling out endorsed hardcoded secrets, client-only authorization, direct input execution, and destructive shell bootstrap guidance.\n47: - Iteration 3: Independent enumeration reconciled the command-owned Markdown scope at 163 lexical entries, executed both core traceability protocols by narrow evidence reads, and classified both overlays as evidence-backed notApplicable without repeating saturated sweeps.\n48: - Iteration 4: Exact maintainability searches isolated six tautological `When to Use` sections; direct reads against the create-skill reference template confirmed one new P2. Narrow counterevidence rereads preserved all four prior findings without duplication, and git history established representative rename lineage for two content-preservation samples.\n49: \n50: ## 7. WHAT FAILED\n51: \n52: - Memory trigger and focused context retrieval timed out at initialization; direct packet evidence is the fallback.\n53: - Iteration 1: `validate_document.py` alone could not prove R3 because its no-numbered-H2 path accepts the malformed Rust reference; validation success was retained as counterevidence rather than treated as conformance proof.\n54: - Iteration 2: An initial directory-level discovery search surfaced six non-Markdown asset files outside the rendered `**/*.md` scope. Those hits were discarded, the search was rerun with `--glob '*.md'`, and no finding relies on the excluded files.\n55: - Iteration 3: Iteration 2's 157-count explanation was disproved. Ripgrep-style discovery omitted six symlink entries; all 163 configured matches are Markdown, representing 160 unique resolved document targets.\n56: - Iteration 4: Two representative rename diffs showed 81% and 90% similarity with substantive body lines retained, but narrow history cannot prove R4 across the other 158 resolved targets; `content_preservation` remains deferred rather than passed.\n57: \n58: ## 8. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n59: \n60: - Runtime behavior and executable security paths: the packet is documentation-only and claims no runtime changes.\n61: \n62: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n63: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n64: ### `checklist_evidence` (core): **failed, carried forward without re-execution** -- the blocked validator-evidence approach was not retried. -- BLOCKED (iteration 2, 1 attempts)\n65: - What was tried: `checklist_evidence` (core): **failed, carried forward without re-execution** -- the blocked validator-evidence approach was not retried.\n66: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n67: - Do NOT retry: `checklist_evidence` (core): **failed, carried forward without re-execution** -- the blocked validator-evidence approach was not retried.\n68: \n69: ### `checklist_evidence` (core): **failed** -- `checklist.md:49` records a real 163/163 validator pass, but that checker does not establish the wrapper invariant for a file with no numbered H2. The completion evidence is therefore insufficient for R3. -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n70: - What was tried: `checklist_evidence` (core): **failed** -- `checklist.md:49` records a real 163/163 validator pass, but that checker does not establish the wrapper invariant for a file with no numbered H2. The completion evidence is therefore insufficient for R3.\n71: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n72: - Do NOT retry: `checklist_evidence` (core): **failed** -- `checklist.md:49` records a real 163/163 validator pass, but that checker does not establish the wrapper invariant for a file with no numbered H2. The completion evidence is therefore insufficient for R3.\n73: \n74: ### `feature_catalog_code` / `playbook_capability` (overlay): **pending** -- not executed in the security dimension; their strategy entries are marked blocked and must not be retried without a later protocol-resolution decision. -- BLOCKED (iteration 2, 1 attempts)\n75: - What was tried: `feature_catalog_code` / `playbook_capability` (overlay): **pending** -- not executed in the security dimension; their strategy entries are marked blocked and must not be retried without a later protocol-resolution decision.\n76: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n77: - Do NOT retry: `feature_catalog_code` / `playbook_capability` (overlay): **pending** -- not executed in the security dimension; their strategy entries are marked blocked and must not be retried without a later protocol-resolution decision.\n78: \n79: ### `feature_catalog_code` / `playbook_capability`: **pending** -- not required for the correctness focus and preserved for a later traceability iteration. -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n80: - What was tried: `feature_catalog_code` / `playbook_capability`: **pending** -- not required for the correctness focus and preserved for a later traceability iteration.\n81: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n82: - Do NOT retry: `feature_catalog_code` / `playbook_capability`: **pending** -- not required for the correctness focus and preserved for a later traceability iteration.\n83: \n84: ### `skill_agent` / `agent_cross_runtime`: **notApplicable** -- the target is a spec-folder/document corpus, not an agent definition. -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n85: - What was tried: `skill_agent` / `agent_cross_runtime`: **notApplicable** -- the target is a spec-folder/document corpus, not an agent definition.\n86: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n87: - Do NOT retry: `skill_agent` / `agent_cross_runtime`: **notApplicable** -- the target is a spec-folder/document corpus, not an agent definition.\n88: \n89: ### `spec_code` (core): **failed, carried forward without re-execution** -- iteration 1's active R3 mismatch remains open; the saturated correctness structural sweep was not repeated. -- BLOCKED (iteration 2, 1 attempts)\n90: - What was tried: `spec_code` (core): **failed, carried forward without re-execution** -- iteration 1's active R3 mismatch remains open; the saturated correctness structural sweep was not repeated.\n91: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n92: - Do NOT retry: `spec_code` (core): **failed, carried forward without re-execution** -- iteration 1's active R3 mismatch remains open; the saturated correctness structural sweep was not repeated.\n93: \n94: ### `spec_code` (core): **failed** -- R3 requires the wrapper on every scoped file, but `interop_errors_and_parity.md:19` begins substantive content without it. The 1-2 sentence intro rule also has seven advisory mismatches. -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n95: - What was tried: `spec_code` (core): **failed** -- R3 requires the wrapper on every scoped file, but `interop_errors_and_parity.md:19` begins substantive content without it. The 1-2 sentence intro rule also has seven advisory mismatches.\n96: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n97: - Do NOT retry: `spec_code` (core): **failed** -- R3 requires the wrapper on every scoped file, but `interop_errors_and_parity.md:19` begins substantive content without it. The 1-2 sentence intro rule also has seven advisory mismatches.\n98: \n99: ### A new traceability finding for the active R3 mismatch: ruled out as a duplicate of `I1-P1-001`; the current read confirms rather than expands it. -- BLOCKED (iteration 3, 1 attempts)\n100: - What was tried: A new traceability finding for the active R3 mismatch: ruled out as a duplicate of `I1-P1-001`; the current read confirms rather than expands it.\n101: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n102: - Do NOT retry: A new traceability finding for the active R3 mismatch: ruled out as a duplicate of `I1-P1-001`; the current read confirms rather than expands it.\n103: \n104: ### Broken scoped navigational Markdown-link class: ruled out by a fenced-code-aware relative-link scan. -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n105: - What was tried: Broken scoped navigational Markdown-link class: ruled out by a fenced-code-aware relative-link scan.\n106: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n107: - Do NOT retry: Broken scoped navigational Markdown-link class: ruled out by a fenced-code-aware relative-link scan.\n108: \n109: ### Client-side-only authorization as approved guidance: ruled out by the explicit server-verification requirement. -- BLOCKED (iteration 2, 1 attempts)\n110: - What was tried: Client-side-only authorization as approved guidance: ruled out by the explicit server-verification requirement.\n111: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n112: - Do NOT retry: Client-side-only authorization as approved guidance: ruled out by the explicit server-verification requirement.\n113: \n114: ### Content-preservation R4: **deferred** -- no pre-transformation manifest/content baseline was available in this iteration; absence of evidence was not converted into a pass. -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n115: - What was tried: Content-preservation R4: **deferred** -- no pre-transformation manifest/content baseline was available in this iteration; absence of evidence was not converted into a pass.\n116: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n117: - Do NOT retry: Content-preservation R4: **deferred** -- no pre-transformation manifest/content baseline was available in this iteration; absence of evidence was not converted into a pass.\n118: - Iteration 4 recovery note: the rendered prompt explicitly authorized a changed, narrow git-history method. Rename commits `dd9e700477384f2b4312f3236428e300b29e840e` and `1922cffed797c62b96e8cf862308232b3f6ba7a8` corroborate preservation for two representatives only; the original full-corpus no-baseline approach remains blocked.\n119: \n120: ### Destructive shell bootstrap guidance in the Markdown scope: ruled out by exact search. -- BLOCKED (iteration 2, 1 attempts)\n121: - What was tried: Destructive shell bootstrap guidance in the Markdown scope: ruled out by exact search.\n122: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n123: - Do NOT retry: Destructive shell bootstrap guidance in the Markdown scope: ruled out by exact search.\n124: \n125: ### Direct execution of user input as approved guidance: ruled out; all matched examples were negative demonstrations. -- BLOCKED (iteration 2, 1 attempts)\n126: - What was tried: Direct execution of user input as approved guidance: ruled out; all matched examples were negative demonstrations.\n127: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n128: - Do NOT retry: Direct execution of user input as approved guidance: ruled out; all matched examples were negative demonstrations.\n129: \n130: ### Endorsed hardcoded-secret guidance: ruled out by exact search plus the direct secret-management read. -- BLOCKED (iteration 2, 1 attempts)\n131: - What was tried: Endorsed hardcoded-secret guidance: ruled out by exact search plus the direct secret-management read.\n132: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n133: - Do NOT retry: Endorsed hardcoded-secret guidance: ruled out by exact search plus the direct secret-management read.\n134: \n135: ### Exact intro/Purpose duplication class: ruled out across 163 files. -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n136: - What was tried: Exact intro/Purpose duplication class: ruled out across 163 files.\n137: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n138: - Do NOT retry: Exact intro/Purpose duplication class: ruled out across 163 files.\n139: \n140: ### Hyphenated scoped filename class: ruled out across 163 files. -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n141: - What was tried: Hyphenated scoped filename class: ruled out across 163 files.\n142: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n143: - Do NOT retry: Hyphenated scoped filename class: ruled out across 163 files.\n144: \n145: ### Missing frontmatter/version class: ruled out across 163 files. -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n146: - What was tried: Missing frontmatter/version class: ruled out across 163 files.\n147: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n148: - Do NOT retry: Missing frontmatter/version class: ruled out across 163 files.\n149: \n150: ### Security evidence: **complete for this iteration** -- each active security finding has direct Markdown file:line evidence and the P1 received an in-iteration skeptic/referee pass. -- BLOCKED (iteration 2, 1 attempts)\n151: - What was tried: Security evidence: **complete for this iteration** -- each active security finding has direct Markdown file:line evidence and the P1 received an in-iteration skeptic/referee pass.\n152: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n153: - Do NOT retry: Security evidence: **complete for this iteration** -- each active security finding has direct Markdown file:line evidence and the P1 received an in-iteration skeptic/referee pass.\n154: \n155: ### The claim that six non-Markdown assets explain the prior discrepancy: ruled out because every one of the 163 matched entries has a `.md` suffix; the discrepancy comes from symlink traversal behavior. -- BLOCKED (iteration 3, 1 attempts)\n156: - What was tried: The claim that six non-Markdown assets explain the prior discrepancy: ruled out because every one of the 163 matched entries has a `.md` suffix; the discrepancy comes from symlink traversal behavior.\n157: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n158: - Do NOT retry: The claim that six non-Markdown assets explain the prior discrepancy: ruled out because every one of the 163 matched entries has a `.md` suffix; the discrepancy comes from symlink traversal behavior.\n159: \n160: ### The claim that the explicit Markdown globs currently match only 157 files: ruled out by independent enumeration of all six configured patterns. -- BLOCKED (iteration 3, 1 attempts)\n161: - What was tried: The claim that the explicit Markdown globs currently match only 157 files: ruled out by independent enumeration of all six configured patterns.\n162: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n163: - Do NOT retry: The claim that the explicit Markdown globs currently match only 157 files: ruled out by independent enumeration of all six configured patterns.\n164: \n165: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n166: \n167: ## 10A. SATURATED / SWEPT DIMENSIONS AND EXPANSION FRONTIER\n168: - Completed pivots: 4\n169: - Failed pivots: 0\n170: - Audited overrides: 0\n171: - Swept: correctness, security, traceability, maintainability\n172: - Pivot lineage: correctness -> security -> traceability -> maintainability\n173: - Remaining frontier: synthesis only\n174: \n175: ## 11. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n176: \n177: - Do not widen into unrelated sk-code skills or runtime implementation.\n178: \n179: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n180: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n181: - Dimension: `synthesis`\n182: - Focus area: consolidate the two active P1s, three active P2s, failed core traceability gates, and deferred content-preservation debt into the planning packet.\n183: - Reason: all four configured dimensions are complete and iteration 4 is the required final pass under `max-iterations`.\n184: - Rotation status: correctness, security, traceability, and maintainability complete; stop the iteration loop.\n185: - Blocked/productive carry-forward: preserve exact finding IDs and the 163-path/160-target distinction; carry the six-instance `When to Use` class once and do not duplicate reconfirmed findings.\n186: - Required evidence: reducer-registry reconciliation, exact file:line citations, and the final conditional verdict with `hasAdvisories=true`.\n187: - Recovery note: `content_preservation` remains deferred for the 158 resolved targets not covered by the two representative rename diffs.\n188: \n189: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n190: \n191: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n192: \n193: ### Bounded Context Snapshot\n194: \n195: - Target pointers: six configured reference/asset roots totaling 163 Markdown path entries and 160 resolved document targets; packet docs are the governing claims.\n196: - Behavior claims: five-field frontmatter, four-part versions, snake_case names, H1/intro/Overview structure, preserved substantive content, and repaired in-hub references.\n197: - Reuse and conventions: create-skill reference/asset templates and `validate_document.py` are the stated authority.\n198: - Review risks and gaps: prior post-ship review remediated duplicated Purpose text and narrowed a broken-link claim; memory MCP timed out; no packet resource map exists.\n199: - Iteration 1 carry-forward: one active P1 wrapper omission; seven advisory intro-length mismatches; R4 content preservation remains unverified without a pre-transformation baseline; prior inventory distribution was stale although its total remained 163.\n200: - Iteration 2 carry-forward: one new P1 for contradictory JavaScript session-cookie guidance and one new P2 for CDN-loader integrity/allowlist hardening.\n201: - Iteration 3 carry-forward: the explicit Markdown globs independently match 163 path entries, not 157; six symlink paths expose three shared workflow documents under both surfaces, yielding 160 resolved targets. Core protocols remain failed on the active R3 mismatch; both overlays are notApplicable by packet scope.\n202: - Iteration 4 carry-forward: six generated `When to Use` sections are too tautological to guide safe selection (new P2); all four prior findings remain active without duplication. Two representative git rename diffs narrow but do not close the R4 preservation debt.\n203: - Out of scope: surface `SKILL.md` header shape and unrelated deep-loop artifacts.\n204: \n205: ## 13. CROSS-REFERENCE STATUS\n206: \n207: | Protocol | Level | Status | Iteration | Notes |\n208: |----------|-------|--------|-----------|-------|\n209: | `spec_code` | core | failed | 1, 3 | Narrow current reread confirms the active R3 wrapper mismatch; no saturated sweep was repeated. |\n210: | `checklist_evidence` | core | failed | 1, 3 | The real 163/163 validator result still does not establish R3 because the current wrapper counterexample remains. |\n211: | `feature_catalog_code` | overlay | notApplicable | 3 | `spec.md:59` excludes feature-catalog files; the packet makes no feature-catalog capability claim. |\n212: | `playbook_capability` | overlay | notApplicable | 3 | `spec.md:59` excludes manual-testing playbooks and `plan.md:26` declares no code/runtime change. |\n213: | `skill_agent` | overlay | notApplicable | - | Target type is spec-folder. |\n214: | `agent_cross_runtime` | overlay | notApplicable | - | Target type is spec-folder. |\n215: \n216: ## 14. FILES UNDER REVIEW\n217: \n218: | Root | Files | Dimensions Reviewed | Status |\n219: |------|------:|---------------------|--------|\n220: | `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/**/*.md` | 50 | correctness, security, traceability, maintainability | reviewed-with-findings |\n221: | `.ope