{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783918550679,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeMi6luqm6mHU9Lf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_itM95odVduAqVuhzgaDv76vV","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/rust/style_guide/interop_errors_and_parity.md","offset":1,"limit":45},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/rust/style_guide/interop_errors_and_parity.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Rust/TypeScript Interop — Errors, Parity & Related Resources\n3: description: Formatting standards, naming conventions, and TypeScript interoperability rules for Rust files in the OpenCode development environment. — Rust/TypeScript Interop — Errors, Parity & Related Resources.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"rust typescript interop errors parity related resources\"\n6:   - \"rust interop errors and parity\"\n7:   - \"rust style guidance\"\n8: importance_tier: normal\n9: contextType: implementation\n10: version: 1.0.0.0\n11: ---\n12: \n13: # Rust/TypeScript Interop — Errors, Parity & Related Resources\n14: \n15: Formatting standards, naming conventions, and TypeScript interoperability rules for Rust files in the OpenCode development environment.\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ### Error Style\n20: \n21: Core public operations return domain-specific `Result` values backed by `thiserror`.\n22: \n23: ```rust\n24: use thiserror::Error;\n25: \n26: #[derive(Debug, Error)]\n27: pub enum RankingError {\n28:     #[error(\"candidate identifier must not be empty\")]\n29:     EmptyIdentifier,\n30: \n31:     #[error(\"candidate score must be finite\")]\n32:     NonFiniteScore,\n33: \n34:     #[error(\"candidate limit {limit} exceeds maximum {maximum}\")]\n35:     LimitExceeded {\n36:         limit: u32,\n37:         maximum: u32,\n38:     },\n39: }\n40: ```\n41: \n42: Rules:\n43: \n44: - Core errors contain adapter-relevant structured context.\n45: - Core errors contain no napi-rs, WASM, or Node runtime types.\n\n(Showing lines 1-45 of 321. Use offset=46 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Rust/TypeScript Interop — Errors, Parity & Related Resources\ndescription: Formatting standards, naming conventions, and TypeScript interoperability rules for Rust files in the OpenCode development environment. — Rust/TypeScript Interop — Errors, Parity & Related Resources.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"rust typescript interop errors parity related resources\"\n  - \"rust interop errors and parity\"\n  - \"rust style guidance\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.0.0.0\n---\n\n# Rust/TypeScript Interop — Errors, Parity & Related Resources\n\nFormatting standards, naming conventions, and TypeScript interoperability rules for Rust files in the OpenCode development environment.\n\n---\n\n### Error Style\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/rust/style_guide/interop_errors_and_parity.md","text":"---\ntitle: Rust/TypeScript Interop — Errors, Parity & Related Resources\ndescription: Formatting standards, naming conventions, and TypeScript interoperability rules for Rust files in the OpenCode development environment. — Rust/TypeScript Interop — Errors, Parity & Related Resources.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"rust typescript interop errors parity related resources\"\n  - \"rust interop errors and parity\"\n  - \"rust style guidance\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.0.0.0\n---\n\n# Rust/TypeScript Interop — Errors, Parity & Related Resources\n\nFormatting standards, naming conventions, and TypeScript interoperability rules for Rust files in the OpenCode development environment.\n\n---\n\n### Error Style\n\nCore public operations return domain-specific `Result` values backed by `thiserror`.\n\n```rust\nuse thiserror::Error;\n\n#[derive(Debug, Error)]\npub enum RankingError {\n    #[error(\"candidate identifier must not be empty\")]\n    EmptyIdentifier,\n\n    #[error(\"candidate score must be finite\")]\n    NonFiniteScore,\n\n    #[error(\"candidate limit {limit} exceeds maximum {maximum}\")]\n    LimitExceeded {\n        limit: u32,\n        maximum: u32,\n    },\n}\n```\n\nRules:\n\n- Core errors contain adapter-relevant structured context.\n- Core errors contain no napi-rs, WASM, or Node runtime types.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":45,"totalLines":321,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/rust/style_guide/interop_errors_and_parity.md","time":{"start":1783918550670,"end":1783918550678}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_072683c7e4594319016a546fd624a48191ad020135b9059f88"}},"id":"prt_f59d4dd6c001jWdsyCwmzz1lTo","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeMi6luqm6mHU9Lf","messageID":"msg_f59d481bf0016YtA9aSM8gMTPt"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783918550685,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeMi6luqm6mHU9Lf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_42ORop6fQ2SgY7e13QW72S7z","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md","offset":82,"limit":30},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n82: **Checklist:**\n83: - [ ] All user input sanitized before display\n84: - [ ] textContent used instead of innerHTML when possible\n85: - [ ] HTML entities escaped in user-generated content\n86: - [ ] Input format validated (email, phone, URL, etc.)\n87: - [ ] No eval() or Function() constructor with user input\n88: \n89: ### CSRF Protection\n90: \n91: **SameSite Cookies:**\n92: ```javascript\n93: // ✅ GOOD: Set SameSite cookie attribute\n94: document.cookie = \"session=abc123; SameSite=Strict; Secure\";\n95: \n96: // ❌ BAD: No SameSite attribute\n97: document.cookie = \"session=abc123\";  // Vulnerable to CSRF\n98: ```\n99: \n100: **CSRF Tokens:**\n101: ```html\n102: <!-- ✅ GOOD: Include CSRF token in forms -->\n103: <form method=\"POST\">\n104:   <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"csrf_token\" value=\"${csrfToken}\">\n105:   <input type=\"text\" name=\"username\">\n106:   <button type=\"submit\">Submit</button>\n107: </form>\n108: \n109: <!-- Server-side verification required -->\n110: ```\n111: \n\n(Showing lines 82-111 of 263. Use offset=112 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"**Checklist:**\n- [ ] All user input sanitized before display\n- [ ] textContent used instead of innerHTML when possible\n- [ ] HTML entities escaped in user-generated content\n- [ ] Input format validated (email, phone, URL, etc.)\n- [ ] No eval() or Function() constructor with user input\n\n### CSRF Protection\n\n**SameSite Cookies:**\n```javascript\n// ✅ GOOD: Set SameSite cookie attribute\ndocument.cookie = \"session=abc123; SameSite=Strict; Secure\";\n\n// ❌ BAD: No SameSite attribute\ndocument.cookie = \"session=abc123\";  // Vulnerable to CSRF\n```\n\n**CSRF Tokens:**\n```html","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md","text":"**Checklist:**\n- [ ] All user input sanitized before display\n- [ ] textContent used instead of innerHTML when possible\n- [ ] HTML entities escaped in user-generated content\n- [ ] Input format validated (email, phone, URL, etc.)\n- [ ] No eval() or Function() constructor with user input\n\n### CSRF Protection\n\n**SameSite Cookies:**\n```javascript\n// ✅ GOOD: Set SameSite cookie attribute\ndocument.cookie = \"session=abc123; SameSite=Strict; Secure\";\n\n// ❌ BAD: No SameSite attribute\ndocument.cookie = \"session=abc123\";  // Vulnerable to CSRF\n```\n\n**CSRF Tokens:**\n```html\n<!-- ✅ GOOD: Include CSRF token in forms -->\n<form method=\"POST\">\n  <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"csrf_token\" value=\"${csrfToken}\">\n  <input type=\"text\" name=\"username\">\n  <button type=\"submit\">Submit</button>\n</form>\n\n<!-- Server-side verification required -->\n```\n","lineStart":82,"lineEnd":111,"totalLines":263,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md","time":{"start":1783918550681,"end":1783918550685}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_072683c7e4594319016a546fd624b88191a3d1e444e53a7cac"}},"id":"prt_f59d4de93001zVp7g23ciVB5yL","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeMi6luqm6mHU9Lf","messageID":"msg_f59d481bf0016YtA9aSM8gMTPt"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783918550702,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeMi6luqm6mHU9Lf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_kVZ7kXr2YcHIaMpj5cTObszR","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md","offset":240,"limit":25},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n240: sessionStorage.setItem('theme', 'dark');  // Non-sensitive data OK\n241: \n242: // ❌ BAD: Store sensitive data\n243: localStorage.setItem('password', user_password);  // Vulnerable to XSS\n244: localStorage.setItem('token', auth_token);  // Accessible to all scripts\n245: ```\n246: \n247: **Cookies:**\n248: ```javascript\n249: // ✅ GOOD: Secure, HttpOnly cookies (server-side)\n250: Set-Cookie: session=abc123; Secure; HttpOnly; SameSite=Strict\n251: \n252: // ❌ BAD: JavaScript-accessible cookies with sensitive data\n253: document.cookie = \"session=abc123\";  // Accessible to XSS\n254: ```\n255: \n256: **Checklist:**\n257: - [ ] No sensitive data in localStorage/sessionStorage\n258: - [ ] Cookies set with Secure, HttpOnly, SameSite attributes\n259: - [ ] Sensitive data encrypted if stored client-side\n260: - [ ] Clear storage on logout\n261: \n262: ---\n263: \n\n(End of file - total 263 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"sessionStorage.setItem('theme', 'dark');  // Non-sensitive data OK\n\n// ❌ BAD: Store sensitive data\nlocalStorage.setItem('password', user_password);  // Vulnerable to XSS\nlocalStorage.setItem('token', auth_token);  // Accessible to all scripts\n```\n\n**Cookies:**\n```javascript\n// ✅ GOOD: Secure, HttpOnly cookies (server-side)\nSet-Cookie: session=abc123; Secure; HttpOnly; SameSite=Strict\n\n// ❌ BAD: JavaScript-accessible cookies with sensitive data\ndocument.cookie = \"session=abc123\";  // Accessible to XSS\n```\n\n**Checklist:**\n- [ ] No sensitive data in localStorage/sessionStorage\n- [ ] Cookies set with Secure, HttpOnly, SameSite attributes\n- [ ] Sensitive data encrypted if stored client-side","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md","text":"sessionStorage.setItem('theme', 'dark');  // Non-sensitive data OK\n\n// ❌ BAD: Store sensitive data\nlocalStorage.setItem('password', user_password);  // Vulnerable to XSS\nlocalStorage.setItem('token', auth_token);  // Accessible to all scripts\n```\n\n**Cookies:**\n```javascript\n// ✅ GOOD: Secure, HttpOnly cookies (server-side)\nSet-Cookie: session=abc123; Secure; HttpOnly; SameSite=Strict\n\n// ❌ BAD: JavaScript-accessible cookies with sensitive data\ndocument.cookie = \"session=abc123\";  // Accessible to XSS\n```\n\n**Checklist:**\n- [ ] No sensitive data in localStorage/sessionStorage\n- [ ] Cookies set with Secure, HttpOnly, SameSite attributes\n- [ ] Sensitive data encrypted if stored client-side\n- [ ] Clear storage on logout\n\n---\n","lineStart":240,"lineEnd":263,"totalLines":263,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/security_patterns/overview_and_checklist.md","time":{"start":1783918550694,"end":1783918550701}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_072683c7e4594319016a546fd624c08191bca990a4fe657f22"}},"id":"prt_f59d4de9a001wn1i8y5c0vOL3I","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeMi6luqm6mHU9Lf","messageID":"msg_f59d481bf0016YtA9aSM8gMTPt"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783918550708,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeMi6luqm6mHU9Lf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_yG7IqE9uRSfapXPMei4M23uQ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/workflow_debug.md","offset":1,"limit":35},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/workflow_debug.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Workflow Reference - Debugging\n3: description: Shared debugging workflow doctrine for sk-code — root-cause diagnosis and scoped repair after a symptom, failing command, runtime error, quality failure, or verification failure, consumed by every surface packet.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"sk-code debugging workflow\"\n6:   - \"debug workflow doctrine\"\n7:   - \"root-cause diagnosis\"\n8:   - \"scoped repair workflow\"\n9: importance_tier: important\n10: contextType: general\n11: version: 1.0.0.1\n12: ---\n13: \n14: # Workflow Reference - Debugging\n15: \n16: Shared debugging workflow doctrine for `sk-code`. This reference covers root-cause diagnosis and scoped repair after a symptom, failing command, runtime error, quality failure, or verification failure appears. It is consumed by surface packets and defines no skill identity or surface-specific standards.\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: ### Purpose\n23: \n24: Debugging is the controlled experiment phase. It reproduces or tightly characterizes the symptom, captures exact evidence, traces the symptom backward to a source cause, applies one-cause fixes, and sends the result back through quality and verification.\n25: \n26: ### When to Use\n27: \n28: - Diagnosing a failing test, build failure, runtime exception, console error, broken interaction, layout regression, command failure, or inconsistent runtime behavior.\n29: - Recovering from failed implementation, failed quality, failed verification, or a concrete regression.\n30: - Tracing a symptom backward before changing code.\n31: - Applying a minimal bug fix to already-scoped files after the root cause is identified.\n32: - Dispatching a bounded parallel investigation when the search space is broad but the symptom is concrete.\n33: - Enforcing the three-strike escalation rule after repeated failed fixes for the same symptom.\n34: \n35: ### When Not to Use\n\n(Showing lines 1-35 of 121. Use offset=36 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Workflow Reference - Debugging\ndescription: Shared debugging workflow doctrine for sk-code — root-cause diagnosis and scoped repair after a symptom, failing command, runtime error, quality failure, or verification failure, consumed by every surface packet.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"sk-code debugging workflow\"\n  - \"debug workflow doctrine\"\n  - \"root-cause diagnosis\"\n  - \"scoped repair workflow\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: general\nversion: 1.0.0.1\n---\n\n# Workflow Reference - Debugging\n\nShared debugging workflow doctrine for `sk-code`. This reference covers root-cause diagnosis and scoped repair after a symptom, failing command, runtime error, quality failure, or verification failure appears. It is consumed by surface packets and defines no skill identity or surface-specific standards.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/workflow_debug.md","text":"---\ntitle: Workflow Reference - Debugging\ndescription: Shared debugging workflow doctrine for sk-code — root-cause diagnosis and scoped repair after a symptom, failing command, runtime error, quality failure, or verification failure, consumed by every surface packet.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"sk-code debugging workflow\"\n  - \"debug workflow doctrine\"\n  - \"root-cause diagnosis\"\n  - \"scoped repair workflow\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: general\nversion: 1.0.0.1\n---\n\n# Workflow Reference - Debugging\n\nShared debugging workflow doctrine for `sk-code`. This reference covers root-cause diagnosis and scoped repair after a symptom, failing command, runtime error, quality failure, or verification failure appears. It is consumed by surface packets and defines no skill identity or surface-specific standards.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDebugging is the controlled experiment phase. It reproduces or tightly characterizes the symptom, captures exact evidence, traces the symptom backward to a source cause, applies one-cause fixes, and sends the result back through quality and verification.\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Diagnosing a failing test, build failure, runtime exception, console error, broken interaction, layout regression, command failure, or inconsistent runtime behavior.\n- Recovering from failed implementation, failed quality, failed verification, or a concrete regression.\n- Tracing a symptom backward before changing code.\n- Applying a minimal bug fix to already-scoped files after the root cause is identified.\n- Dispatching a bounded parallel investigation when the search space is broad but the symptom is concrete.\n- Enforcing the three-strike escalation rule after repeated failed fixes for the same symptom.\n\n### When Not to Use","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":35,"totalLines":121,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-opencode/references/workflow_debug.md","time":{"start":1783918550704,"end":1783918550707}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_072683c7e4594319016a546fd624c88191815a2b189d096cb2"}},"id":"prt_f59d4dea7001vNbDVKZ34ASJc6","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeMi6luqm6mHU9Lf","messageID":"msg_f59d481bf0016YtA9aSM8gMTPt"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783918550715,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeMi6luqm6mHU9Lf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_w6meJAr9e3opGMg0GIXeiiCu","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/third_party_integrations/best_practices_and_summary.md","offset":15,"limit":50},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/third_party_integrations/best_practices_and_summary.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n15: \n16: Reference guide for integrating external JavaScript libraries in Webflow projects, with production-tested patterns. — Best Practices, Library Summary & Related.\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: ### Purpose\n23: \n24: Cross-library best practices for third-party integrations, plus a summary of the supported libraries and what each one is for.\n25: \n26: ### When to Use\n27: \n28: Use this reference when implementing or troubleshooting best practices, library summary & related.\n29: \n30: ---\n31: \n32: ## 2. BEST PRACTICES\n33: \n34: ### CDN Loading Pattern\n35: \n36: ```javascript\n37: // ✅ Good: Version pinned, async, error handled\n38: const CDN_URL = 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/library@{version}';\n39: \n40: async function load_with_timeout(url, timeout_ms = 10000) {\n41:   return new Promise((resolve) => {\n42:     const timer = setTimeout(() => resolve(false), timeout_ms);\n43:     \n44:     const script = document.createElement('script');\n45:     script.src = url;\n46:     script.async = true;\n47:     script.onload = () => { clearTimeout(timer); resolve(true); };\n48:     script.onerror = () => { clearTimeout(timer); resolve(false); };\n49:     document.head.appendChild(script);\n50:   });\n51: }\n52: \n53: // ❌ Bad: No version, no error handling\n54: document.write('<script src=\"https://cdn.example.com/lib.js\"></script>');\n55: ```\n56: \n57: ### Version Pinning\n58: \n59: ```javascript\n60: // ✅ Pinned to specific version (check HTML source for current versions)\n61: 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/hls.js@{major.minor.patch}'\n62: \n63: // ✅ Pinned to specific minor version\n64: 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@studio-freight/lenis@{major.minor}'\n\n(Showing lines 15-64 of 172. Use offset=65 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\nReference guide for integrating external JavaScript libraries in Webflow projects, with production-tested patterns. — Best Practices, Library Summary & Related.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nCross-library best practices for third-party integrations, plus a summary of the supported libraries and what each one is for.\n\n### When to Use\n\nUse this reference when implementing or troubleshooting best practices, library summary & related.\n\n---\n\n## 2. BEST PRACTICES\n\n### CDN Loading Pattern","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/third_party_integrations/best_practices_and_summary.md","text":"\nReference guide for integrating external JavaScript libraries in Webflow projects, with production-tested patterns. — Best Practices, Library Summary & Related.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nCross-library best practices for third-party integrations, plus a summary of the supported libraries and what each one is for.\n\n### When to Use\n\nUse this reference when implementing or troubleshooting best practices, library summary & related.\n\n---\n\n## 2. BEST PRACTICES\n\n### CDN Loading Pattern\n\n```javascript\n// ✅ Good: Version pinned, async, error handled\nconst CDN_URL = 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/library@{version}';\n\nasync function load_with_timeout(url, timeout_ms = 10000) {\n  return new Promise((resolve) => {\n    const timer = setTimeout(() => resolve(false), timeout_ms);\n    \n    const script = document.createElement('script');\n    script.src = url;\n    script.async = true;\n    script.onload = () => { clearTimeout(timer); resolve(true); };\n    script.onerror = () => { clearTimeout(timer); resolve(false); };\n    document.head.appendChild(script);\n  });\n}\n\n// ❌ Bad: No version, no error handling\ndocument.write('<script src=\"https://cdn.example.com/lib.js\"></script>');\n```\n\n### Version Pinning\n\n```javascript\n// ✅ Pinned to specific version (check HTML source for current versions)\n'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/hls.js@{major.minor.patch}'\n\n// ✅ Pinned to specific minor version\n'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@studio-freight/lenis@{major.minor}'","lineStart":15,"lineEnd":64,"totalLines":172,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-webflow/references/implementation/third_party_integrations/best_practices_and_summary.md","time":{"start":1783918550712,"end":1783918550715}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_072683c7e4594319016a546fd624d08191ba1985b7fff57d80"}},"id":"prt_f59d4deb1001y6yc6K3zOWRunW","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeMi6luqm6mHU9Lf","messageID":"msg_f59d481bf0016YtA9aSM8gMTPt"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783918550727,"sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeMi6luqm6mHU9Lf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_7BKLuEBrltWO7afzjpuHiMLw","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/assets/skill/skill_reference_template.md","offset":95,"limit":25},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/assets/skill/skill_reference_template.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n95: \n96: ---\n97: \n98: \\## 1. OVERVIEW\n99: \n100: ### Purpose\n101: Provides systematic workflows for analyzing changes, filtering artifacts, and creating well-structured commits.\n102: \n103: ### When to Use\n104: - Creating commits with multiple file changes\n105: - Filtering generated files from commits\n106: - Writing clear commit messages\n107: \n108: ### Core Principle\n109: Atomic commits with clear intent + filtered artifacts = maintainable Git history.\n110: ```\n111: \n112: #### BAD Intro Structure (duplicates content)\n113: \n114: ```markdown\n115: # Git Commit Workflows\n116: \n117: Step-by-step workflows for creating clean, atomic commits with proper filtering.\n118: \n119: ### Core Principle   ← WRONG: No headers in intro!\n\n(Showing lines 95-119 of 1025. Use offset=120 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\n---\n\n\\## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\nProvides systematic workflows for analyzing changes, filtering artifacts, and creating well-structured commits.\n\n### When to Use\n- Creating commits with multiple file changes\n- Filtering generated files from commits\n- Writing clear commit messages\n\n### Core Principle\nAtomic commits with clear intent + filtered artifacts = maintainable Git history.\n```\n\n#### BAD Intro Structure (duplicates content)\n\n```markdown","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/assets/skill/skill_reference_template.md","text":"\n---\n\n\\## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\nProvides systematic workflows for analyzing changes, filtering artifacts, and creating well-structured commits.\n\n### When to Use\n- Creating commits with multiple file changes\n- Filtering generated files from commits\n- Writing clear commit messages\n\n### Core Principle\nAtomic commits with clear intent + filtered artifacts = maintainable Git history.\n```\n\n#### BAD Intro Structure (duplicates content)\n\n```markdown\n# Git Commit Workflows\n\nStep-by-step workflows for creating clean, atomic commits with proper filtering.\n\n### Core Principle   ← WRONG: No headers in intro!","lineStart":95,"lineEnd":119,"totalLines":1025,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-doc/create-skill/assets/skill/skill_reference_template.md","time":{"start":1783918550718,"end":1783918550726}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_072683c7e4594319016a546fd624d48191bdaa03e0e99d981e"}},"id":"prt_f59d4deb9001enNVrg0DsC1ehF","sessionID":"ses_0a65ac472ffeMi6luqm6mHU9Lf","messageID":"msg_f59d481bf0016YtA9aSM8gMTPt"}}
